ade and kin networks. Allan McDougall, Lisa Philips, and Daniel Boxberger explore fundamental questions of state formation, social transformation, and the (re)construction of identity to expose the narratives and other devices of nation building, their impact on generations caught in the transition, and the reverberations of those national myths that continue to the present.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBorderlandszNorthwest, PacificxHistory. 0aBoundariesxSocial aspectszNorthwest, Pacific. 0aCanadians. 0aHegemonyzNorthwest, PacificxHistory. 0aNational characteristics, American. 0aNational characteristics, Canadian. 7aHISTORY / North America.2bisacsh1 aBoxberger, Daniel L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBoxberger, Daniel L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcDougall, Allan K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhilips, Lisa, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPhilips, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311141792940uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483669240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774836692423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774836692/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-141792-9  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles